    <h1>Cruises &#x2022; Dream Cruises look&#xAD;ing into ar&#xAD;eas for im&#xAD;prove&#xAD;ment</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201128/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-28"><time>2020-11-28</time></a>
        - <span>FORUM</span>
        - <span role="byline">Michael Goh&#xD;&#xA;Pres&#xAD;i&#xAD;dent of Dream Cruises and Head of In&#xAD;ter&#xAD;na&#xAD;tional Sales&#xD;&#xA;Gent&#xAD;ing Cruise Lines</span>
    </section>

    <p>On be­half of Dream Cruises, we first thank Ms Lil­ian Lim for shar­ing her feed­back and high­light­ing her ex­pe­ri­ence (Rude cruise am­bas­sadors ru­ined travel ex­pe­ri­ence, Nov 24).</p>
    <p>We value the feed­back of our guests, as we con­tinue to pro­vide our sig­na­ture ser­vice ex­cel­lence, with safety be­ing our para­mount pri­or­ity.</p>
    <p>We ap­pre­ci­ate the con­struc­tive feed­back high­lighted by Ms Lim and are look­ing into ar­eas for im­prove­ment with re­gard to our Dream Cruises am­bas­sadors, who have gone through train­ing to dis­play a pro­fes­sional dis­po­si­tion while en­sur­ing that all guests adhere to safe man­age­ment mea­sures at all times.</p>
    <p>We also thank her for shar­ing her pos­i­tive com­ments about what made her trip pleas­ant.</p>
    <p>We have com­mu­ni­cated with Ms Lim to fur­ther un­der­stand the de­tails, and have taken nec­es­sary steps to re­in­force ser­vice ex­cel­lence in our daily train­ing of all crew. We will con­tinue to do our best in pro­vid­ing the best cruis­ing ex­pe­ri­ence for our guests.</p>


